  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung 860 EVO SSD is missing from the ata_device_blacklist array (around line 4564-4565) where similar models (Samsung SSD 840 and 850) are marked with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. This flag is essential for disabling queued TRIM operations which the Samsung 860 EVO cannot properly handle, resulting in 20-30 second lockups with SEND FPDMA QUEUED timeout errors. The ata_dev_blacklisted() function (line 4620) matches device model numbers against the blacklist and returns horkage flags. The missing Samsung 860 entry means the device doesn't get the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag, preventing the ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() function (line 2218) from disabling queued TRIM support."
}

